Python 3 Wall of Superpowers

Python 3.0 was released 2,761 days ago on December 3, 2008.

As listed on PyPI - packages in green support Python 3, packages in red do not. Hopefully one day everything will be greener.

  • Written by Yuv aka ubershmekel.
  • Don't wait, start porting code to Python 3.
  • Get the source for this GAE app at github.
  • The wall updates almost once a day, see the timestamps in the html.
  • Design stolen from HTML5 Boilerplate.
  • If a module is red though it supports Python 3 it's because the PyPI record does not have the "Programming Language :: Python :: 3" tag. Consider contacting the package maintainer to add this trove classifier to the package's PyPI record.
  • Note that this subdomain's called "python3wos" - when the status was below 50%, the title of the site was "Python 3 Wall of Shame". I kid you not.
